They are also historically a big German fund operator. We expect them to continue that. And they look for opportunities both internationally and domestically, not in our core business, but in other forms of real estate. So I think between essentially kind of the historical separate account business, they have their premier fund, plus their German fund business, and then our adding to that platform in terms of owning 50% of the business, I think it will be attractive for institutional and retail investors, not retail real estate investors, but retail investors to potentially want to want to have Jamestown invest in real estate for them.

