David Simon -- Chairman, President, and Chief Executive Officer

Well, again, I wouldn't focus too much on quarter over quarter. There is volatility in our numbers because of overage rent and other factors, write-off like Regal, which is highly unusual that it would manifest itself in a material number, but it's important to point out. So look, I think you have to go back to the beginning of the year where we thought because '21 was a really banner year. And we were very conservative in our comp NOI estimate of 2%.

We're blowing through that number. We'll see what the fourth quarter brings. But it's -- our comp NOI growth is going to be really strong, and we continue to expect it to grow next year as well. So you've got to look at this over a two- or three-year period as opposed to quarter over quarter or even year over year, and we're making a tremendous amount of progress.

Remember, we were one of the few industries that were literally mandated the shutdown, and we're kind of back up and running and producing results. that are pre-pandemic, which is very good to see. And we'll expect to see comp NOI growth next year even in the face of a potential recession.

Michael Goldsmith -- UBS -- Analyst

